gle legal and cultural tool meant to address conflict across a wide variety of cultures can have the perverse effect of exacerbating the problems that plague the communities cited as falling short.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFreedom of religion. 0aReligion and politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  areligion, religious studies, freedom, justice, peace, persecution, public, private, laws, legal issues, litigation, policies, cultural, culture, epistemology, epistemological, assumptions, politics, political, analysis, critique, critical, academic, scholarly, research, project, global, world, contributors, essay collection, anthology, hebrew, christian, african, traditional, apartheid.1 aAgrama, Hussein Ali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmien, Waheeda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaman, Lori G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBender, Courtney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastelli, Elizabeth A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChatterjee, Nandini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanchin, Peter G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanchin, Peter G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHackett, Rosalind I. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaefeli, Evan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHefner, Robert W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurd, Elizabeth Shakman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHu